e0b53a29-cac7-517d-a980-5cc3310e242f,tg:rubgr:1784,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"

[recto] Ad [Addendum] Good Shepherd. Christ for Good Shepherd with lamb on his shoulders by Heemskerck in drawing Agnus Dei, 1549. On left the Baptist pointing to the lamb in the centre and to Christ as Shepherd on the right. L. [Leon] Preibisz, [= Martin van Heemskerck: ein Beitrag zur Geschichte des Romanismus in der niederländischen Malerei des XVI. Jahrhunderts, Leipzig: Klinkhart & Biermann], 1911, p. 92, N° 98. No print knwon after this, see STATENS MUSEUM FOR KUNST, Den Kongelige Kobberstiksamling, Tegninger af Maerten van Heemskerck, catalogue by J. [Jan] Garff, Kopenhagen 1971, N° 24, pl. 24; [verso] Bruegel's engraving of 1565 of the Good Shepherd (B. 122) seems to be directly based on Heemskerck's Good Shepherd.

On left the Baptist pointing to the lamb in the centre and to Christ as Shepherd on the right. L. [Leon] Preibisz, [= Martin van Heemskerck: ein Beitrag zur Geschichte des Romanismus in der niederländischen Malerei des XVI. Jahrhunderts, Leipzig: Klinkhart & Biermann], 1911, p. 92, N° 98. <part_of.title>Good Shepherd: Stridbeck, fig. 54, probably developed from Bruegel's engraving late 16th century, Stridbeck, fig. 54. See also Stridbeck, p. 256 for Unfaithful Shepherd.</part_of.title>
